üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£ Git Installation & Configuration

| Command                                          | Single Line Explanation                   |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------- |
| `git --version`                                  | Displays installed Git version            |
| `git config --global user.name "YourName"`       | Sets global username                      |
| `git config --global user.email "you@email.com"` | Sets global email                         |
| `git config --list`                              | Shows all Git configurations              |
| `git config --local user.name "Name"`            | Sets username for current repository only |


üî• 2Ô∏è‚É£ Repository Management

| Command                       | Single Line Explanation                           |
| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `git init`                    | Initializes new Git repository                    |
| `git clone <repo-url>`        | Copies remote repository locally                  |
| `git clone --bare <repo-url>` | Creates bare repository without working directory |



üî• 3Ô∏è‚É£ Git File Lifecycle

| Command              | Single Line Explanation                |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `git status`         | Shows file status in working directory |
| `git add <file>`     | Adds file to staging area              |
| `git add .`          | Adds all changes to staging area       |
| `git restore <file>` | Discards changes in working directory  |
| `git rm <file>`      | Removes file from Git tracking         |



üî• 4Ô∏è‚É£ Commit & History

| Command                    | Single Line Explanation          |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `git commit -m "message"`  | Creates commit with message      |
| `git commit -am "message"` | Adds and commits tracked files   |
| `git log`                  | Shows commit history             |
| `git log --oneline`        | Shows compact commit history     |
| `git show <commit-id>`     | Shows details of specific commit |
| `git diff`                 | Shows unstaged changes           |
| `git diff --staged`        | Shows staged changes             |


üî• 5Ô∏è‚É£ Branching

| Command                  | Single Line Explanation            |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| `git branch`             | Lists local branches               |
| `git branch <name>`      | Creates new branch                 |
| `git checkout <branch>`  | Switches branch                    |
| `git switch <branch>`    | Switches branch (modern command)   |
| `git checkout -b <name>` | Creates and switches to new branch |
| `git branch -d <name>`   | Deletes branch                     |
| `git branch -D <name>`   | Force deletes branch               |



üî• 6Ô∏è‚É£ Merging & Rebasing

| Command                      | Single Line Explanation                    |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `git merge <branch>`         | Merges branch into current branch          |
| `git merge --no-ff <branch>` | Forces merge commit                        |
| `git rebase <branch>`        | Rebases current branch onto another        |
| `git rebase --abort`         | Cancels rebase process                     |
| `git rebase --continue`      | Continues rebase after conflict resolution |



üî• 7Ô∏è‚É£ Handling Conflicts

| Command          | Single Line Explanation                  |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `git status`     | Shows conflicted files                   |
| `git add <file>` | Marks conflict as resolved               |
| `git commit`     | Finalizes merge after resolving conflict |



üî• 8Ô∏è‚É£ Reset, Revert & Checkout

| Command                    | Single Line Explanation                      |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| `git reset --soft HEAD~1`  | Removes last commit but keeps changes staged |
| `git reset --mixed HEAD~1` | Removes last commit and unstages changes     |
| `git reset --hard HEAD~1`  | Deletes last commit and changes permanently  |
| `git revert <commit-id>`   | Creates new commit reversing changes         |
| `git checkout <commit-id>` | Moves to specific commit (detached HEAD)     |




üî• 9Ô∏è‚É£ Git Stash

| Command           | Single Line Explanation               |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `git stash`       | Temporarily saves uncommitted changes |
| `git stash list`  | Lists stashed changes                 |
| `git stash apply` | Applies latest stash                  |
| `git stash pop`   | Applies and removes stash             |
| `git stash drop`  | Deletes specific stash                |


üî• üîü Tags

| Command                        | Single Line Explanation |
| ------------------------------ | ----------------------- |
| `git tag`                      | Lists all tags          |
| `git tag v1.0`                 | Creates lightweight tag |
| `git tag -a v1.0 -m "release"` | Creates annotated tag   |
| `git push origin v1.0`         | Pushes tag to remote    |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ .gitignore & Clean

| Command                  | Single Line Explanation               |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------- |
| `touch .gitignore`       | Creates ignore file                   |
| `git clean -fd`          | Deletes untracked files and folders   |
| `git rm --cached <file>` | Stops tracking file but keeps locally |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Remote Repositories

| Command                       | Single Line Explanation         |
| ----------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `git remote -v`               | Shows remote repository URLs    |
| `git remote add origin <url>` | Adds remote repository          |
| `git fetch`                   | Downloads changes from remote   |
| `git pull`                    | Fetches and merges changes      |
| `git push`                    | Pushes changes to remote        |
| `git push -u origin <branch>` | Pushes and sets upstream branch |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£3Ô∏è‚É£ GitHub Pull Requests Flow


| Command                          | Single Line Explanation  |
| -------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `git clone <fork-url>`           | Clones forked repository |
| `git checkout -b feature-branch` | Creates feature branch   |
| `git push origin feature-branch` | Pushes branch to GitHub  |
| `git pull origin main`           | Syncs with main branch   |


üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ SSH & Authentication


| Command                                                  | Single Line Explanation |
| -------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096`                              | Generates SSH key       |
| `cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub`                                  | Displays public key     |
| `git remote set-url origin git@github.com:user/repo.git` | Switches to SSH remote  |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£5Ô∏è‚É£ GitHub Actions (Basic)

| Command                            | Single Line Explanation          |
| ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `mkdir -p .github/workflows`       | Creates workflow directory       |
| `touch .github/workflows/main.yml` | Creates workflow file            |
| `git push`                         | Triggers GitHub Actions workflow |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ Troubleshooting


| Command                                 | Single Line Explanation         |
| --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `git reflog`                            | Shows history of HEAD movements |
| `git checkout -b recovered <commit-id>` | Recovers deleted branch         |
| `git push --force`                      | Force pushes changes            |
| `git branch --show-current`             | Shows current branch            |
| `git fsck`                              | Checks repository integrity     |



üî• 1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ Git in DevOps


| Use Case              | Command                      |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| CI/CD Trigger         | `git push`                   |
| GitOps deployment     | `git commit && git push`     |
| Tag-based release     | `git tag && git push --tags` |
| Sync fork             | `git fetch upstream`         |
| Multi-branch workflow | `git checkout -b feature`    |





